        Overrides:
        obtain in class org.mini2Dx.gdx.utils.Pool<T>

      • free

        public void free(T object)
        Puts the specified object in the pool, making it eligible to be returned by obtain(). If the pool already contains Pool.max free objects, the specified object is reset but not added to the pool.

        The pool does not check if an object is already freed, so the same object must not be freed multiple times.

        Overrides:
        free in class org.mini2Dx.gdx.utils.Pool<T>
        Parameters:
        object -

      • reset

        protected void reset(T object)
        Called when an object is freed to clear the state of the object for possible later reuse. The default implementation calls Poolable#reset() if the object is Poolable.
        Overrides:
        reset in class org.mini2Dx.gdx.utils.Pool<T>
        Parameters:
        object -

      • freeAll

        public void freeAll(org.mini2Dx.gdx.utils.Array<T> objects)
        Puts the specified objects in the pool. Null objects within the array are silently ignored.

        The pool does not check if an object is already freed, so the same object must not be freed multiple times.

        Overrides:
        freeAll in class org.mini2Dx.gdx.utils.Pool<T>
